# Tailwind CSS v4 Guidelines

## Configuration
- Tailwind config is in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
- Using Tailwind CSS v4 with PostCSS integration
- Content paths include all JS/JSX files in src/

## Class Usage
- Use utility classes for styling
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Use state variants: `hover:`, `focus:`, `active:`, `disabled:`

## Common Patterns
- Layout: `flex`, `grid`, `block`, `inline-block`
- Spacing: `p-*`, `m-*`, `space-*`
- Colors: Use semantic color names when possible
- Typography: `text-*`, `font-*`, `leading-*`

## Custom CSS
- Only add custom CSS when Tailwind utilities are insufficient
- Use CSS custom properties for dynamic values
- Keep custom styles minimal and focused